ACL = Access Control List

//mkdir data
//ls -l data 
//useradd u1
//groupadd g1
//id u1//useradd u2
//usermod -G g1 u2
//chown u1:g1 data
//ls -ld data
//getfacl data --adding additional user and giving him specific permissions
//set facl -m u:u2:rw data
//setfacl -m g:devops:rws data
//getfacl data 
//gpasswd -d u2 g2  --- remove user from group 


Special permissions

suid  are use to run executable files by normal user as well as root user

